            . I am an <rs id="t18070114-2-viclabel7" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070114-2-victim70 t18070114-2-viclabel7"></join>, I live in <placeName id="t18070114-2-crimeloc8">Foster lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18070114-2-crimeloc8" type="placeName" value="Foster lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18070114-2-crimeloc8" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070114-2-off5 t18070114-2-crimeloc8"></join>. On the 22nd of December, between three and four o'clock, I was up stairs at dinner; the young man in the shop came up to me and said, that a man in the shop had stole some goods from off the counter. I went down stairs, I turned the prisoner round, put my hand in his pocket, and took out a parcel containing the brass pulleys. I took him into the counting-house, left him in the custody of my brother, and turned the key upon him. He let fall the brass nobs from his other pocket while I was sending for a constable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18070114-2-person72">
                  JOHN 
                  GOODING
               <interp inst="t18070114-2-person72" type="surname" value="GOODING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070114-2-person72" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070114-2-person72" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Knight.</p>
               <p>Q. Has Mr. Knight any partners - A. Yes, his brother Richard. When 
               <persName id="t18070114-2-person73">
                  John 
                  Lemmon
               <interp inst="t18070114-2-person73" type="surname" value="Lemmon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070114-2-person73" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070114-2-person73" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came in the shop, there were about seven or eight customers in the shop, he did not ask for any thing, I suspected him; I saw him with a parcel of brass pulleys in his pocket. I informed my master of it. When he came he took the brass pullies out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The brass pullies belong to me, only the brass nobs belong to him; I beg for mercy.</p>
               <p>(The property produced and identified.)</p>
